<2ND_LINE>PM-Taxi Killing,0245</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Passenger Horrified as Gunman Kills Cabbie</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Rubert is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A taxi cab passenger watched in horror as a gunman
forced his way into the car and shot the driver to death, police
said.
   The passenger, a Chicago man who was being driven Wednesday from
Miami International Airport to the downtown Hyatt Regency Hotel,
told police the gunman jumped into the cab when driver Rubert
Fleurimon slowed down in the Liberty City section. The gunman then
fatally shot the 37-year-old Fleurimon and jumped out while the cab
was still rolling.
   The gunman's motive was not known.
   ``Apparently he didn't stop fast enough and was shot in the back
of the head,'' said Detective Mike Gonzalez. ``We don't know what he
was doing in Liberty City. The passenger doesn't know either. He
isn't familiar with Miami.''
   Robert Emery, a Yellow Cab operations manager, said the normal
route from the airport to the hotel does not go through Liberty
City, a high crime area.
   The cab swerved out of control and crashed as Fleurimon sat dying
in the driver's seat. When the passenger tried to pull his briefcase
out of the cab, someone in a gathering crowd stole it, Gonzalez said.
   Other people escorted the man for four or five blocks to a phone
where he called another cab, Gonzalez said. Then the passenger,
whose name was not released, called police from the hotel.

</TEXT>
