<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Korea-Lawmakers     12-15 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Korea-Lawmakers,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Legislators Increase Own Pay By 85 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In a rare show of unity, ruling and
opposition lawmakers today approved without debate legislation that
will raise their salaries by 85 percent on Jan. 1.
   The two-minute action raised a lawmaker's monthly salary from the
current $2,550 to $4,730, bringing their pay to the level of Cabinet
ministers.
   The bill was approved by the National Assembly's Budget
Settlement Committee. It's passage by the full assembly will be a
mere formality.
   Many South Koreans criticized the steep pay increase as
unethical, citing the meager incomes of most factory workers and
high inflation.
   According to industry figures, a footwear assembly line worker
with five years of job experience makes about $550 a month,
including allowances.
</TEXT>
