<HEAD>Doctors Say Toddler Rushed To Hospital Had Ingested Cocaine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 2{-year-old girl was taken to a hospital
suffering from hallucinations and seizures apparently caused by a
cocaine overdose, authorities said today.
   The child was taken to Cedars-Sinai Medical Center shortly after
9 p.m. Wednesday, said police Sgt. K. Davis.
   A urinalysis revealed the child had ingested cocaine, said
hospital spokeswoman Paula Correia. The toddler was listed in fair
condition in the medical center's pediatric intensive-care unit, Ms.
Correia said.
   Police and officials from the Department of Children's Services
were investigating, Davis said.
   ``The parents are saying they don't know how it all happened,''
he said. ``The mother said she dropped off the girl at her sister's,
who then dropped off the girl at a day care center.''
   The parents, who weren't identified, told police they noticed the
child acting strangely when they picked her up from the center,
Davis said.
   Sgt. Craig Crosby said the child was picked up by an ambulance at
a day care center after a caller reported the child was having a
seizure.
   He said he did not know the name of the day care center, which is
located in south-central Los Angeles, an area notorious for gangs
and drug dealing. The child's family also lives in the area.
