<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     12-15 0681</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0700</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow from Nevada to New England; Hurricane-force Winds in Utah,
California</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A large band of winter weather scattered snow from Nevada to New
England today, piling up foot-and-a-half accumulations in Upper
Michigan and combining with gusty winds in the mountains of Colorado
and Wyoming.
   Hurricane-force winds wreaked havoc in northern Utah and northern
California late Wednesday and early today.
   Winds felled trees, caused small power outages and blew at least
five trucks off Interstate 15 near Salt Lake City. An observer in
Centerville early today measured gusts of at least 104 mph _ the
maximum his equipment would register.
   Strong winds blew through northern Utah's canyons, with gusts of
82 mph reported at Centerville and Smithville. Numerous
semi-trailers were blown off Interstate 15 near Farmington. A high
wind warning was in effect for the western slopes of the Wasatch
Mountains.
   In northern California, winds toppled trees into homes and parked
cars, blew out windows and knocked out power to more than 100,000
customers of Pacific Gas & Electric Co., company officials said.
Gusts up to 80 mph were recorded at the top of Mount Diablo.
   Colorado received the heaviest snow in the West, with up to 7{
inches recorded near Boulder and 3-6 inches in Colorado Springs.
Gusty winds reduced visibility and hampered travel in the northeast
foothills of the Colorado Rockies, and a winter storm warning was in
effect for the area.
   A winter storm warning also was issued for the southern mountains
of Wyoming. Five inches of snow fell at Lander by late Wednesday and
gusts up to 45 mph occurred at Rock Springs.
   Western Kansas also had blowing snow, and snow advisories were
posted for the northwest Texas Panhandle and east central Nevada.
   Cold arctic winds produced lake-effect snow over the southern
shores of Lake Superior. Eighteen inches fell near Wakefield in
Upper Michigan. Snow and strong winds reduced visibilities in
northwest parts of Lower Michigan.
   Heavy snow warnings remained in effect for parts of Upper
Michigan.
   Light snow also fell in parts of New England and eastern New York
state. Eastern Texas and western Louisiana received light rain.
   Today's forecast called for snow in much of Nevada, the central
and southern Rockies, the western edge of the southern and central
Plains, with the heaviest snow on the eastern slopes of the Colorado
Rockies, Michigan, the lower Great Lakes, the central and northern
Appalachians and northern New England; rain from southeast Texas to
the Gulf Coast and the southern Applachians, with a few
thunderstorms over the central Gulf Coast; and rain along the
Southern California coast.
   Temperatures were expected to remain below zero in northern
Minnesota and northeastern North Dakota. Highs were expected to be
in the single digits and teens from the northern Great Lakes to the
northern Plains and central Rockies; the 20s and 30s in northern New
England, the lower Great Lakes, the Ohio and Mississippi valleys,
northwest Texas, and western Montana; in the 60s and 70s in the
south Atlantic Coast states, the Gulf Coast, and from southern
Arizona to the central and southern coasts of California; and in the
40s and 50s elsewhere.
   At 2 a.m. EST, temperatures ranged from 15 degrees below zero at
Devils Lake, N.D., to 73 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 49 cloudy; Boston 39 cloudy; Buffalo 39 windy;
Charleston, S.C. 44 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 33 partly cloudy;
Cleveland 36 cloudy; Detroit 32 windy; Miami 71 cloudy; New York 38
cloudy; Philadelphia 38 cloudy; Pittsburgh 39 windy; Portland, Maine
36 rain; Washington 46 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck fair; Chicago 30 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 50
cloudy; Denver 19 snow; Des Moines 17 partly cloudy; Indianapolis 34
partly cloudy; Kansas City 25 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul windy;
Nashville 47 windy; New Orleans 57 partly cloudy; St. Louis 30 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 42 windy; Anchorage 27 cloudy; Las Vegas 50
windy; Los Angeles 56 cloudy; Phoenix 54 partly cloudy; Salt Lake
City 32 cloudy; San Diego 57 cloudy; San Francisco 52 windy; Seattle
35 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 27 snow; Toronto 34 windy.
</TEXT>
