<HEAD>Locusts Attack Southern Jordan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMMAN, Jordan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Locusts have invaded southern Jordan and the
kingdom is taking steps to combat them, the government said Thursday.
   Salem Lawzi, Agriculture Ministry undersecretary, told state-run
Radio Jordan that one swarm of locusts covered four square miles of
the Al-Mudawarah area along the southern border with Saudi Arabia on
Thursday.
   He said another swarm covered one square mile of As-Saheb
Al-Asmar, also along the southern border. He did not report the
extent of damage.
   Lawzi said the ministry and the army were combating the locusts
with pesticides. He called on other nations and the United Nations
for assistance.
   Many nations, especially in northern Africa, have reported being
attacked by unusually large swarms of locusts this year.
