<HEAD>Cruise Missile Elimination Ends</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The last of 43 ground-launched cruise
missiles currently scheduled for destruction under the
Intermediate-Range Nuclear Forces Treaty was eliminated Thursday at
Davis-Monthan Air Force Base.
   Capt. Mark Besich, an Air Force spokesman, said the last missile
and sixth and final transporter erector launcher slated to be cut in
half occurred during the morning, with the inspection by a 13-member
Soviet team officially over at 9:15 a.m.
   He said the Soviets subsequently began writing their inspection
reports and would return to Travis Air Force Base near San Francisco
either Thursday night or Friday morning.
   An initial 41 missiles were similarly cut lengthwise in half in
October.
</TEXT>
