<FILEID>AP-NR-12-15-88 1419EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Rangel-Castro     12-15 0288</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Rangel-Castro,280</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lawmaker Says Cooperation With Cuba on Drug Control Possible</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chairman of the House Committee on
Narcotics Abuse and Control said Thursday that after a lengthy
conversation with Cuban President Fidel Castro he is convinced the
possibility exists to establish ``a new era of cooperation in
narcotics control.''
   Rep. Charles Rangel, D-N.Y., said his 3{-hour meeting with Castro
in Havana on Tuesday evening was ``extremely promising.''
   ``There is now the possibility of discussions towards
establishing direct Cuba-U.S. cooperation in narcotics
interdiction,'' as well as extending cooperation into other areas
such as eemergency search and rescue operations, Rangel said.
   ``It is time to depoliticize narcotics efforts with Cuba,''
Rangel said. He said the meeting with Castro signals the possibility
of ``opening a new era of cooperation in narcotics control.''
   Rangel commented in a statement issued by his office here. He and
others in a 12-member congressional delegation are touring Latin
America, with visits scheduled to the Dominican Republic, Guyana,
Trinidad and Tobago.
   Rangel said Castro told the delegation that Cuba wants to work
with the United States and Latin American countries ``and that
cooperation with the United States will naturally flow from this
involvement.''
   ``Castro said he recognizes that the problem is shared by the
region, and it needs to be addressed regionally,'' Rangel said.
   Currently there is no cooperation, officially or unofficially,
between Marxist Cuba and the United States on narcotics matters.
   Rangel said he had been told by State Department and Drug
Enforcement Administration officials that Cuban and U.S. law
enforcement agencies ``do not even share information on suspected
upcoming drug shipments.''
   ``This kind of nuts-and-bolts joint interdiction cooperation is
an example of what can be started right away,'' he said.
</TEXT>
