<TEXT>
   Shirley Temple Black, famous for her
rendition of ``The Good Ship Lollipop'' as a child movie star, will
christen a 212-passenger liner Saturday as the Seabourn Pride.
   The ship is owned by Seabourn Cruise Line, a new San
Francisco-based company launched by Warren Titus, retired head of
Royal Viking Line.
