<DOCNO> AP881215-0162 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-15-88 1945EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r p AM-DemocraticChairman     12-15 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Democratic Chairman,160</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Rep. Michael Barnes of Maryland has
written top Democrats announcing his candidacy for chairman of the
national party, an aide said Thursday.
   Barnes, for eight years a congressman from suburban Washington,
D.C., becomes the fourth candidate in the race to succeed retiring
Democratic National Chairman Paul Kirk.
   Already in the race are Ronald Brown, former top aide to Jesse
Jackson; former Rep. James Jones of Oklahoma and Michigan state
party chairman Richard Wiener.
   ``The Democratic Party is a sometimes fragile coalition. Our next
chairman mnust be able to reach out to all elements of our party,
seek common ground and build consensus,'' Barnes said.
   He made the comment in a letter that aide Jeff Heller said was
sent Wednesday to the more than 400 members of the committee and
other top Democrats around the country. The DNC members are to vote
on a new chairman when they meet in Washington on Feb. 9 and 10.
</TEXT>
