<HEAD>Romanian Economist Asks For Political Asylum</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ionita Olteanu, a leading Romanian
economist and journalist, has requested political asylum in West
Germany, a Munich newspaper reported Thursday.
   The Sueddeutsche Zeitung said Olteanu was invited to Munich to
take part in a panel discussion on Bavarian television Tuesday. The
Romanian Embassy ordered him not to take part because Romanian
exiles and human rights activists also were participating, it said.
   Olteanu, editor of the Romanian business weekly magazine Revista
Economia, left his Munich hotel Wednesday and asked Bavarian
authorities for asylum, the paper reported.
   Late last week, Maria Cosma, 38, coach of the Romanian women's
gymnastics team, defected in Hamburg and is planning to apply for
political asylum, the West German Gymnastics Federation said.
   Ms. Cosma, who is expected to get a coaching job with the West
German women's gymnastics team, coached the Romanian women at the
Summer Olympics in Seoul and guided the team to an upset victory
over the Soviet Union at the 1987 World Championships in Rotterdam.
</TEXT>
