<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Britain-Collision     12-15 0114</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Collision,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviet, West German Vessels Collide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet tanker and a West German container ship
collided in the Thames estuary in dense fog early Thursday, but
little damage resulted, the coast guard said.
   A coast guard spokesman, who by custom was not identified, said,
``There was no damage to cargo or personnel and no pollution.'' He
said an investigation was under way.
   The collision, about 15 miles off Harwich, northeast of London,
involved the 10,000-ton Soviet tanker Konstantin Tsiolkovskiy and
the 10,000-ton West German container vessel Proud Eagle.
   The spokesman said the container ship proceeded to Felixstowe,
while the tanker was at anchor waiting for a berth at Coryton.
</TEXT>
