<HEAD>Lebanese Man Arrested At JFK</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: NEW throughout to UPDATE with suspect not confirmed brother
of
former Lebanese president</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Lebanese man was arrested Thursday at Kennedy
International Airport on charges he tried to smuggle almost five
pounds of heroin into the country, federal authorities said.
   Gebrayel Sarkis, 70, was arrested by agents of the U.S. Customs
Service following a flight from Geneva, said Ann Driscoll, a
