<HEAD>Jobless Rate Falls to 7.5 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unemployment in Britain fell to a seasonally
adjusted 7.5 percent of the workforce in November, the lowest level
since March 1981, the government said Thursday.
   The November figure was down from 7.7 percent in October and
substantially lower than the 9.2 percent rate in November 1987, the
Department of Employment said.
   Seasonally adjusted unemployment was estimated at 2.11 million
people, down from a revised 2.16 million people in October and 2.6
million people in November 1987.
   The department said the decline in the number of jobless of
49,300 was consistent with the average 40,000-a-month fall since the
beginning of 1988.
