<1ST_LINE>r f BC-AutoProdn     12-15 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Only version planned.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
260,617 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
263,042 but up from last year, Ward's Automotive Reports said
Thursday.
   In the same week a year ago, 215,714 cars and light trucks were
produced, the trade journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 167,998 cars this week,
compared with 167,477 a week ago and 132,504 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 92,619,
compared with last week's 95,565 and last year's 83,210.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,883 cars this week, up from
17,866 a week ago but down from last year's 22,280.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,335, compared
with 21,705 a week ago and 18,345 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
