<HEAD>Financing Company Settles Age Discrimination Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of the country's largest companies that
finances mobile homes and recreation vehicles has agreed to pay
$115,000 to settle Federal Trade Commission charges involving
discrimination against the elderly, the FTC said Thursday.
   Green Tree Acceptance Inc., of Minneapolis, was charged with
violating federal credit laws by failing to give some consumers a
reason for denying them credit and by informing others only that
they failed to meet unspecified internal credit standards.
   An amended complaint included the additional charge that the
company required elderly applicants to make higher down payments.
The FTC said the proposed consent decree is for settlement purposes
only and doesn't constitute an admission by the company that it
violated the law.
