<2ND_LINE>BC-Du Pont-Hercules,0234</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Du Pont Purchases Carpet Fiber Division</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Du Pont Co. signed a letter of intent to
purchase Hercules Inc.'s olefin carpet fiber business, doubling its
share of the international market for the cheap commercial carpet
fibers, a Du Pont spokesman announced Thursday.
   The purchase price was not disclosed, said Tom McAndrews,
director of the flooring systems division.
   Du Pont accounted for about $2 billion of the $20 billion
commercial and residential carpet market sales in 1988, McAndrews
said.
   The acquisition of the Hercules business, reported to sell $50
million to $60 million annually, will expand Du Pont's share of the
$400 million olefin fiber market to more than $100 million,
McAndrews said.
   Du Pont announced last month it planned to begin making olefin
fibers as part of a new program to market commercial carpets sold
through retail outlets.
   Under a supply cotract, Hercules will continue producing olefine
carpet fibers at near capacity for three to five years, according to
a company statement. Du Pont will have exclusive rights to that
production, after which time it plans to have expanded its capacity,
the company said.
   Du Pont also will obtain rights to Hercules' customer list and
marketing information, the company said.
   Du Pont is a diversified chemical, specialty products and energy
company with 1987 sales of $30.5 billion.
</TEXT>
